# Implementation Guidelines - Orbito Platform

## Backend Implementation

### Controllers

- Inherit from BaseController
- Use policy-based authorization
- Return Result<T> pattern
- Handle errors consistently
- Apply proper HTTP status codes

### Commands/Queries

- One handler per operation
- Validate with FluentValidation
- Include TenantId in all operations
- Use async/await throughout
- Log operations with correlation ID

### Repositories

- Always inject ITenantContext for tenant-scoped entities
- Use GetByIdForClientAsync pattern for security
- Mark unsafe methods as Obsolete
- Apply query filters for tenant isolation
- Include cancellation tokens

### Services

- Keep stateless
- Use dependency injection
- Handle Stripe webhooks idempotently
- Implement retry logic for external calls
- Log all external interactions

### Database

- Use migrations for schema changes
- Apply unique constraints for business rules
- Index foreign keys and search fields
- Use filtered indexes where appropriate
- Configure cascade deletes carefully

## Frontend Implementation

### Components

- Use function components with hooks
- Keep under 500 lines
- Extract complex logic to custom hooks
- Implement loading and error states
- Use shadcn/ui for consistency

### Data Fetching

- Use React Query for all API calls
- Implement optimistic updates
- Cache data appropriately (5-10 min)
- Handle pagination on backend
- Show loading skeletons

### Forms

- React Hook Form + Zod validation
- Match backend validation rules
- Show inline error messages
- Disable submit during processing
- Clear form on success

### State Management

- Zustand for global state
- React Query for server state
- Local state for UI-only concerns
- Avoid prop drilling
- Keep stores focused

### Authentication

- NextAuth for session management
- Check roles in middleware
- Refresh tokens automatically
- Handle 401 globally
- Redirect to login when needed

### API Integration

- Use axios with interceptors
- Add auth headers automatically
- Log requests in development
- Handle errors consistently
- Show user-friendly messages

## Security Implementation

### Authentication

- JWT with 15min access token
- 7-day refresh token
- Store tokens securely
- Validate on every request
- Include tenant claims

### Authorization

- Policy-based, not role-based
- Check at controller level
- Verify in business logic
- Audit sensitive operations
- Log authorization failures

### Data Access

- Filter by TenantId always
- Verify ownership in repositories
- No cross-tenant queries
- Sanitize all inputs
- Escape output properly

### Payment Security

- Verify Stripe signatures
- Implement idempotency
- Lock during processing
- Audit all transactions
- Handle webhooks async

## Performance Guidelines

### Backend

- Use async/await for I/O
- Implement caching strategically
- Paginate large datasets
- Use projection for queries
- Avoid N+1 problems

### Frontend

- Lazy load routes
- Optimize images
- Minimize bundle size
- Use React.memo wisely
- Implement virtual scrolling

### Database

- Index search columns
- Use includes to prevent round trips
- Batch operations when possible
- Monitor slow queries
- Regular maintenance

## Testing Requirements

### Unit Tests

- Test business logic
- Mock external dependencies
- Use AAA pattern
- Assert specific outcomes
- Cover edge cases

### Integration Tests

- Test API endpoints
- Use test database
- Verify full flow
- Check authorization
- Test error scenarios

### Frontend Tests

- Test critical user flows
- Mock API responses
- Verify form validation
- Check error handling
- Test accessibility

## Deployment Process

### Pre-deployment

- Run all tests
- Check migrations
- Update configuration
- Verify environment variables
- Backup database

### Deployment

- Use blue-green strategy
- Monitor error rates
- Check health endpoints
- Verify integrations
- Test critical paths

### Post-deployment

- Monitor logs
- Check performance metrics
- Verify webhook processing
- Test payment flow
- Update documentation

## Code Quality Standards

- No commented code in production
- No TODO comments in releases
- Maximum 20-30 lines per method
- Descriptive variable names
- Consistent formatting
- Document complex logic
- Regular refactoring
